# This is the SHA-256 of synthetic_data/synthetic_db.sqlite produced by
# the canonical run on the original dev machine using:
#
#   - Python 3.14 (Homebrew)
#   - SEED = 42 (gen_data.py)
#   - --n-patients all (uses every DE-SynPUF Sample 1 BENE_ID, ~116k)
#   - DE-SynPUF Sample 1 + CMS Synthetic RIF 2023 inputs
#
# Equality of this hash on a fresh regeneration means the entire build
# is byte-deterministic — a strong signal that the regenerated artifact
# is faithful, but NOT strictly required for behavioral pass.
#
# Behavioral pass requires only:
#   - 25/25 named tests pass in synthetic_data/tests/
#   - row counts in evidence/row_counts_v1.json match within ±5%
#
# Different SQLite versions or different Python versions can produce
# byte-different but behaviorally-identical output. Don't rely on the
# hash as a hard gate.
